# With NO project home, export falls back to stdout and creates NO `.sporo/` tree. Export's
# original contract was side-effect-free — a stranger reading an official recipe from a bare
# directory just wants the text, and must never have a project scaffolded underfoot. The
# default file-write is for authors in their own repo; the corpus reader gets stdout.
exec sporo export derived-progress-report
stdout '## Adopt it here'
stdout '## Report back'
! stdout 'sporo export: wrote'
! exists .sporo
